{"id": "EUVD-2022-54953", "enisaUuid": "a6eb42cd-e653-32dd-b5f5-e2a04cc30cd8", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nrtc: pl031: fix rtc features null pointer dereference\n\nWhen there is no interrupt line, rtc alarm feature is disabled.\n\nThe clearing of the alarm feature bit was being done prior to allocations\nof ldata->rtc device, resulting in a null pointer dereference.\n\nClear RTC_FEATURE_ALARM after the rtc device is allocated.", "datePublished": "2025-02-26T01:56:19", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-01T19:47:02", "baseScore": 5.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/cd2722e411e8ab7e5ae41102f6925fa13dffdac5", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/d274ce4a3dfd0b9a292667535578359b865765cb", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/1b915703964f7e636961df04c540261dc55c6c70", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/ea6af39f3da50c86367a71eb3cc674ade3ed244c"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-49273"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.04, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0480a27f-18fb-3d01-8d45-5628dc10ad27", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.17.2"}, {"id": "42bf4618-b670-3a80-a230-1a7de295cc5e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.12"}, {"id": "4a59e12f-2ae2-3dd1-850c-106a340f8cf0", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.33"}, {"id": "52e12645-67a2-3d49-95dd-7ac6f10e302d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "d9b0dd54a1943f47a381a474f8ea2c94466110c0 <cd2722e411e8ab7e5ae41102f6925fa13dffdac5"}, {"id": "54940394-d1c2-38eb-8ea3-176b8a5a1563", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.18"}, {"id": "81962d56-1554-3e07-a743-791ac15216b6", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "d9b0dd54a1943f47a381a474f8ea2c94466110c0 <ea6af39f3da50c86367a71eb3cc674ade3ed244c"}, {"id": "d6436a2e-3842-363f-9e00-53d2c714c1c1", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patc